","elementId":"dl3uSs4Y0J8GiFZU6PIgH","fixedPoint":[0.85952035063906873,0.85952035063906984]},"endArrowhead":"arrow","opacity":100,"updated":1772704418409,"locked":false,"points":[[0,0],[297.46916366805567,181.78671113047812]],"version":88,"elbowed":false,"type":"arrow","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"ai","roundness":{"type":2},"lastCommittedPoint":null,"height":181.78671113047812,"link":null,"startArrowhead":null,"strokeColor":"#1971c2","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"endBinding":{"mode":"orbit","elementId":"tv9IV3wY-lAHAwyON_qdb","fixedPoint":[0.22310075183843051,0.77689924816156675]},"versionNonce":721107068,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-365.19863824167805,"angle":0,"y":634.87031724617736,"width":297.46916366805567},{"seed":2001911292,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"hwQWvcRS9knPtfe7CEAAZ","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"startBinding":{"mode":"orbit","elementId":"tv9IV3wY-lAHAwyON_qdb","fixedPoint":[0.91841098043330205,0.081589019566688945]},"endArrowhead":"arrow","opacity":100,"updated":1772704418409,"locked":false,"points":[[0,0],[234.41557192591017,-595.05491335038732]],"version":75,"elbowed":false,"type":"arrow","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"aj","roundness":{"type":2},"lastCommittedPoint":null,"height":595.05491335038732,"link":null,"startArrowhead":null,"strokeColor":"#1971c2","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"endBinding":{"mode":"orbit","elementId":"VgibRLOkxSX4jPdVARB6P","fixedPoint":[0.18838360635025483,0.50009999999999999]},"versionNonce":2144312644,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":76.475839761105817,"angle":0,"y":731.81035153289986,"width":234.41557192591017},{"seed":247570044,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"JEf6bOgtI6cqA6-S9eL7g","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":20,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1772704418409,"locked":false,"text":"Challenges\n\n1. Unnecessarily increasing load on posts db\n\n\n\nInstead pull model we can implement push model\n\n- Whenever a new post got created an event is published to the queue\n- feed workers will consume this event and add post to the followers feed\n\nChallenges\n\n- Celebreties will have huge number of followers\nadding this post to every follower is not a good approach.\n\n**** Hybrid Approach ***\n\n- <1000 followers then we can go with push model\n- else (for celebreties) pull model.\n\n\n- post created event publised to the queue\n- feed worker consumes and validate whether this user is celebrity or not.\n- If not celebrity\n    - Fetch all followers\n    - Update their feed cache \n        - FIFO queue (500 limit) \n        - followerId: (postId,authorId)\n- If celebrity skip updating followers\n\n\n*** End to End Feed Request ***\n\n- User initiates feed request (20 posts limit)\n- Feed request lands on the feed service.\n- Feed service fetches top (20 posts) from feed cache.\n- Feed service fetches celebrityIds\n- Feed service queries post db with celebrityIds and fetched recent top 20 posts.\n- merge and rank and pick top 20 posts\n- return back to the user\n\n- subsequent request flow\n\n    - user sends nextCursor value ( timestamp ) \n    - take this timestamp and query feed cache and get top 20 posts\n    - Feed service fetches celebrityIds\n    - take this timestamp and celebrityIds and query post db and get top 20 posts\n    - merge and rank and pick top 20 posts\n    - return back to the user\n\n\n","version":1485,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"ak","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Challenges\n\n1. Unnecessarily increasing load on posts db\n\n\n\nInstead pull model we can implement push model\n\n- Whenever a new post got created an event is published to the queue\n- feed workers will consume this event and add post to the followers feed\n\nChallenges\n\n- Celebreties will have huge number of followers\nadding this post to every follower is not a good approach.\n\n**** Hybrid Approach ***\n\n- <1000 followers then we can go with push model\n- else (for celebreties) pull model.\n\n\n- post created event publised to the queue\n- feed worker consumes and validate whether this user is celebrity or not.\n- If not celebrity\n    - Fetch all followers\n    - Update their feed cache \n        - FIFO queue (500 limit) \n        - followerId: (postId,authorId)\n- If celebrity skip updating followers\n\n\n*** End to End Feed Request ***\n\n- User initiates feed request (20 posts limit)\n- Feed request lands on the feed service.\n- Feed service fetches top (20 posts) from feed cache.\n- Feed service fetches celebrityIds\n- Feed service queries post db with celebrityIds and fetched recent top 20 posts.\n- merge and rank and pick top 20 posts\n- return back to the user\n\n- subsequent request flow\n\n    - user sends nextCursor value ( timestamp ) \n    - take this timestamp and query feed cache and get top 20 posts\n    - Feed service fetches celebrityIds\n    - take this timestamp and celebrityIds and query post db and get top 20 posts\n    - merge and rank and pick top 20 posts\n    - return back to the user\n\n\n","height":1325,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#1e1e1e","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1551288572,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":8,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-1441.1540433862679,"angle":0,"y":1153.8948765380132,"width":891},{"seed":109080316,"roughness":1,"id":"dYUFbiCSU_BTO6upwa8WI","strokeWidth":1,"isDeleted":false,"strokeStyle":"solid","startBinding":null,"endArrowhead":null,"opacity":100,"updated":1772704418409,"points":[[0,0],[0,81.24504586319145],[1.777062999357842,95.937110042488229],[13.975545169118597,101.33520266828153],[32.245950078908578,105.6036749382846],[51.728985227062111,106.70598204429881],[68.362900608740844,105.6069084227593],[83.964224179182196,102.88989158362904],[99.525371886428275,95.35807376427104],[100.58910440204657,81.24504586319145],[101.43255738417912,11.066502392818677],[100.15182896713623,-0.353787502790